meanings.definition: To make a strong, lasting impression on someone.
meanings.sent1: The magician's trick really overimpressed the audience.
meanings.sent2: The movie's plot twist overimpressed the viewers.
meanings.sent3: The puppy's attempt to do a backflip overimpressed everyone.
meanings.sent4: The beauty of the sunset overimpressed her, leaving her speechless.
meanings.sent5: The grandeur of the cathedral's architecture overimpressed the tourists.

meanings.definition: To be excessively influenced or affected by something.
meanings.sent1: She was overimpressed by the celebrity's extravagant lifestyle.
meanings.sent2: He tends to get overimpressed by flashy advertisements.
meanings.sent3: The cat seemed overimpressed by the laser pointer's red dot.
meanings.sent4: The young artist was overimpressed by the works of the masters.
meanings.sent5: The child was overimpressed by the size of the dinosaur skeleton at the museum.
